<Text>I am partial to this parish. My sister got married here, my kids, nephews, and nice did their first communion and confirmation here and it happens to be walking distance from from my parents home. Having said that, what is most important is that this is the a House of God and like all parishes, the parishioners are the people that make this a beautiful church (parish). Within the relatively small city of Irwindale, California, it attract people from nearby and far away cities. Last year, the parish celebrated 50 years since the Archdiocese of Los Angeles distinguished her as an independent parish, and the new church built and dedicated on March 22, 2009 celebrated it's 5th anniversary. This is truly a warm and welcoming parish.<//Text>< Pics>

<Review>*Update at bottom* I tried on dresses in June, and that day was a good experience. They allowed me to have 9 people (I paid to rent out the store for an hour and a half). We brought snacks and mimosas. Christine helped me, and while she did make me feel a bit pressured into buying the dress, I really do love the dress. It is much more expensive than I ever thought I would pay for a dress ($1,700). She told me It just came in the store and I was the first bride to try it on, and that they could hold onto the dress until I paid it off with no interest. She made it very easy to say yes.

My wedding is in May 2021, so I wasn't in a rush to pick up the dress, but I got a phone call from the bridal box 2 days ago telling me they usually only hold dressed for 30 days and they want me to finish paying off the dress to make more room for them. (definitely did not mention that before - now making me feel pressured to pay faster) So, yesterday I pulled out the rest of the money and went to the store to pay it off and bring it home. When I got there a woman with red hair helped me. She said she is the only employee working there right now and that "even the owner had to step away because she was having some serious issues" (Whatever that means).

When she pulled my dress out of the back room, I immediately noticed the built in bra area was falling apart in multiple areas. The threading was unraveling, and and the bra part was sagging down and not connected to the front anymore. It was absolutely not in that condition what I originally bought the dress. I tried it on twice, and have multiple witnesses. Its very noticeable.

I told the woman helping me and she said no-one should have tried it on after me because once I put a deposit on it because its considered my property. So I asked her then how this could have gotten like this since I was the only one try try it on. She tells me that the dress was there weeks before me and I was not the first, or only one to try it on. She did not feel sympathetic of my situation, did not offer me an apology or anything to try to make this situation better. **To the owner: Please talk to your employees and remind them that wedding dress shopping is a really special thing for a bride. I will not be recommending this dress boutique any longer. Which is sad, because it could have been a fantastic experience.

< Review>
After visiting a major bridal chain, we walked in to our 2 o‚Äôclock appointment at the Bridal Box not expecting the outcome that transpired. I am an older bride and this is my second wedding so to say that I had anxiety about trying on dresses is putting it lightly. My girlfriend and I had pretty much decided on a dress at the other store and she had taken photos. Thank God she did.
The dresses we saw at the Bridal Box were absolutely stunning. I have an athletic build and usually wear size 6-8 so I wasn‚Äôt anticipating that each dress I choose would look amazing and they did. It‚Äôs like trying on bikinis and then showing all your friends the flaws you can pick on on your body. This however, was different. Every dress fit and fit beautifully. It was a rare moment. Having Kim there to assist made the process easy and comfortable. I am no girly girl so what happened next really shocked me. I had narrowed down my choices to two dresses.
The moment I tried the second Rebecca Ingram dress on and walked out, my girlfriend started to well up and I started to cry. I felt absolutely beautiful.  Kim started to cry and the owner came in asking if we were saying yes to the dress because she wanted to ring the bell! I felt like I was starring in a tv show. It was beautifully surreal. I sat in my dress for a little longer and the owner brought us some champagne.
